1. Experiment aim clearly states the purpose of the exercise (1 point) - The aim of the experiment should be explicitly stated in a clear and concise manner.
2. Experiment aim includes specific tasks and objectives (1 point) - Each exercise should have clearly defined tasks and objectives that are to be accomplished in the experiment.
3. Experiment aim includes expected outcomes or results (1 point) - The aim should outline what the expected outcomes or results of the experiment are.
4. Experiment aim demonstrates relevance to the report title or subject (1 point) - The aim should directly relate to the report title and subject, ensuring that it is relevant to the overall topic of the report.
5. Experiment aim includes sufficient detail to guide the experiment (1 point) - The aim should provide enough detail to guide the execution of the experiment, ensuring that the tasks and objectives are clear and precise.